    "answers": [
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/gZiIA.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 9671656,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 7176382,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/7176382/shubhendu-pramanik",
                "reputation": 2761,
                "display_name": "Shubhendu Pramanik"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 4,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1533540697,
            "creation_date": 1533540697,
            "body": "<p>Because when the line  <code>Image ii=new Image();<\/code> gets executed inside <code>main<\/code> it creates instance of <code>Image<\/code> and inside which you've written line <code>Image i=new Image();<\/code><\/p>\n\n<p>Which means you keep creating new <code>Image<\/code> instances repeatedly.<\/p>\n\n<p>Just keep it like <code>Image i;<\/code> and initialize it on need basis.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 51702590,
            "question_id": 51702553
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/0e26cfe3ac75cd582ca200fbc6fa0421?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 112612,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 296974,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/296974/glglgl",
                "reputation": 91543,
                "display_name": "glglgl",
                "accept_rate": 100
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1533540739,
            "creation_date": 1533540739,
            "body": "<p>As soon as you instantiate an object of class <code>Image<\/code>, it is started to be created. Along this process, it receives a field <code>i<\/code> of type <code>Image<\/code>, which is initialized with a new object of class <code>Image<\/code>. This one gets initialized again, and so on.<\/p>\n\n<p>Just remove that line <code>Image i=new Image();<\/code>.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 51702596,
            "question_id": 51702553
        }
    ],
